    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-wine-700 mb-2">What's the difference between Merlot and Cabernet Sauvignon for beginners?</h3>
    <p class="text-gray-700">Merlot offers softer tannins and a more approachable entry point than Cabernet Sauvignon, with rounder fruit flavors like plum and cherry rather than blackcurrant. The key difference lies in Merlot's earlier ripening cycle, which produces wines with lower acidity and a silkier mouthfeel. While Cabernet Sauvignon can be austere when young, Merlot is typically ready to drink upon release, making it ideal for those new to red wine.</p>
